    "core_content": {
      "parsing_res_list": [
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "The Quotient Rule ",
          "block_bbox": [
            65,
            91,
            1460,
            234
          ],
          "block_id": 0,
          "block_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "SO ",
          "block_bbox": [
            6,
            422,
            143,
            494
          ],
          "block_id": 1,
          "block_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\frac{d}{d x}\\Bigg(\\frac{u}{v}\\Bigg)=\\operatorname*{l i m}_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{\\Delta(u/v)}{\\Delta x}=\\operatorname*{l i m}_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{v\\displaystyle\\frac{\\Delta u}{\\Delta x}-u\\displaystyle\\frac{\\Delta v}{\\Delta x}}{v(v+\\Delta v)}1\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            659,
            543,
            2268,
            858
          ],
          "block_id": 2,
          "block_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "As $\\Delta x\\to0,\\Delta v\\to0$ also,because $v=g(x)$ is differentiable and therefore continuous.\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            0,
            1034,
            2828,
            1264
          ],
          "block_id": 3,
          "block_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "Thus, using the Limit Laws, we get ",
          "block_bbox": [
            0,
            1480,
            1718,
            1607
          ],
          "block_id": 4,
          "block_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\frac{d}{dx}\\left(\\frac{u}{v}\\right)=\\frac{v\\lim\\limits_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{\\Delta u}{\\Delta x}-u\\lim\\limits_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{\\Delta v}{\\Delta x}}{v\\lim\\limits_{\\Delta x\\to0}(v+\\Delta v)}=\\frac{v\\frac{du}{dx}-u\\frac{dv}{dx}}{v^2}",
          "block_bbox": [
            290,
            1748,
            2590,
            2197
          ],
          "block_id": 5,
          "block_order": 6
        }
      ],
      "markdown": "## The Quotient Rule \n\nSO \n\n$$\\frac{d}{d x}\\Bigg(\\frac{u}{v}\\Bigg)=\\operatorname*{l i m}_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{\\Delta(u/v)}{\\Delta x}=\\operatorname*{l i m}_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{v\\displaystyle\\frac{\\Delta u}{\\Delta x}-u\\displaystyle\\frac{\\Delta v}{\\Delta x}}{v(v+\\Delta v)}1\n$$\n\nAs $\\Delta x\\to0,\\Delta v\\to0$ also,because $v=g(x)$ is differentiable and therefore continuous.\n\n\n\nThus, using the Limit Laws, we get \n\n$$\\frac{d}{dx}\\left(\\frac{u}{v}\\right)=\\frac{v\\lim\\limits_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{\\Delta u}{\\Delta x}-u\\lim\\limits_{\\Delta x\\to0}\\frac{\\Delta v}{\\Delta x}}{v\\lim\\limits_{\\Delta x\\to0}(v+\\Delta v)}=\\frac{v\\frac{du}{dx}-u\\frac{dv}{dx}}{v^2}$$",
